{
  "stem": "7094.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The smell of food, I used to faint because we were so hungry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the same time, as I told you, my father was already in concentration camp, so I had the responsibility-- my grandmother came back because it was easier to be in Sadowa Wisznia at that time than in Lvov, so she came back with the unmarried sister-- daughter.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had both of families to look after.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after work, I used to take off my arm band and go to the village, which was-- anybody could shoot me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was on-- on-- on a death sentence, because you were forbidden and there was no but.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Human life had-- didn't represent any value.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the moods, if they didn't like your face.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They could hit you, they-- There wasn't-- you-- you didn't have any sense of protection of the law or justice.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were completely in the hand of-- of-- of-- of the Germans or the Ukrainian police who was there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But necessity was so great that I just used to take off the band and used to go to a village and exchange whatever we had, soap or clothes, whatever, a tablecloth, anything, for a pound of grain, for a half of loaf of bread.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to come back home and my mother used to mince the grain on the coffee machine.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We used to grind and make some soup.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was a daily occurrence.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took the-- the risk one had to in order to survive it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In bigger town, which I've learned later, you know, they were-- they were better organized.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had some schools.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had not very much, but at least-- In small towns like Sadowa Wisznia, you depended entirely on your own resources, and you were forbidden.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
